WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:15.000
Downloaded From AnimeArcadia.lk

00:06.105 --> 00:08.105
-[alarms wailing]
-[bystanders clamoring]

00:08.188 --> 00:09.771
[distressing music playing]

00:11.730 --> 00:13.438
[Sentry] It's impossible.

00:14.396 --> 00:16.105
[Patriot] We're demon hunters.

00:16.688 --> 00:19.855
Getting killed by the impossible's
an everyday hazard.

00:19.938 --> 00:21.355
This time is different.

00:21.438 --> 00:25.063
We have no recorded cases
of any demon higher than Type 2.

00:25.146 --> 00:28.146
But these demons, what they could do…

00:28.230 --> 00:31.646
Their power level marks them as Type 4s.

00:31.730 --> 00:32.646
At least.

00:33.230 --> 00:36.771
The real question is,
where's this apocalypse at, huh?

00:36.855 --> 00:38.938
After all the hype,
I'm almost disappointed.

00:39.021 --> 00:40.063
Whatcha mean?

00:40.146 --> 00:43.730
I mean, the Rabbit has Sparda's sword
and both halves of the amulet.

00:43.813 --> 00:47.230
That's everything it needs
to blow our world wide open.

00:47.313 --> 00:49.563
So, why is this wall still standing?

00:49.646 --> 00:51.313
[Mary] You can ask it in person.

00:52.271 --> 00:54.396
The amulet stopped a few miles north.

00:54.480 --> 00:58.688
This dumbfuck devil spawn
has no idea it's leading us right to it.

01:00.396 --> 01:02.855
Grab what you need, we leave in 60.

01:06.605 --> 01:09.105
-[Mary] I'll admit I had doubts about you.
-[cocks gun]

01:10.271 --> 01:13.105
But the way you charged in
to take the Rabbit on solo…

01:13.188 --> 01:16.563
You've got some elite-sized balls.
Can you stand?

01:17.480 --> 01:20.146
100%, Lieutenant. Absolutely. Good to go.

01:20.730 --> 01:21.896
[grunts]

01:21.980 --> 01:23.730
Maybe just a little longer.

01:23.813 --> 01:26.063
Sit tight. We'll call Evac for you.

01:26.146 --> 01:28.230
[agent] I can take his place, Lieutenant.

01:28.813 --> 01:32.313
That blast from the Rabbit's sword
laid me out, but I'm good now.

01:32.896 --> 01:35.146
I want to see this mission
through to the end.

01:35.230 --> 01:37.230
[suspenseful music playing]

01:42.105 --> 01:43.855
-[energy crackles]
-[trilling] Shh.

01:43.938 --> 01:44.938
[gasps]

01:47.688 --> 01:50.063
If you hadn't gotten me out of the way…

01:50.146 --> 01:51.146
I know.

01:51.688 --> 01:54.771
Just try a little harder
not to get yourself killed this time.

01:54.855 --> 01:56.021
All right?

01:56.105 --> 01:57.021
No promises.

02:01.146 --> 02:03.813
Let's go get this
carrot-munching motherfucker.

02:13.480 --> 02:15.771
["Rollin' (Air Raid Vehicle)"
by Limp Bizkit playing]

02:15.855 --> 02:17.146
♪ Throw your hands up ♪

02:17.230 --> 02:19.730
♪ Your… your… your hands up ♪

02:19.813 --> 02:22.730
♪ Throw your hands up
Throw your hands up ♪

02:22.813 --> 02:25.730
♪ Move in, now move out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

02:25.813 --> 02:27.896
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

02:27.980 --> 02:30.605
♪ Breathe in, now breathe out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

02:30.688 --> 02:32.771
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

02:32.855 --> 02:35.563
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

02:35.646 --> 02:37.980
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

02:38.063 --> 02:40.480
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

02:40.563 --> 02:42.980
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

02:43.063 --> 02:45.188
♪ Hey, ladies, hey, fellas ♪

02:45.271 --> 02:48.063
♪ And the people that don't give a **** ♪

02:48.146 --> 02:50.230
♪ All the lovers, all the haters ♪

02:50.313 --> 02:53.063
♪ And all the people
That call themselves players ♪

02:53.146 --> 02:55.146
♪ Hot mommas, pimp daddies ♪

02:55.230 --> 02:58.146
♪ And the people rollin' up in Caddies ♪

02:58.230 --> 03:00.646
♪ Hey, rockers, hip-hoppers ♪

03:00.730 --> 03:02.896
♪ And everybody all around the world ♪

03:02.980 --> 03:05.646
♪ Move in, now move out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

03:05.730 --> 03:08.146
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

03:08.230 --> 03:10.355
♪ Breathe in, now breathe out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

03:10.438 --> 03:13.230
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

03:13.313 --> 03:15.438
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

03:15.521 --> 03:18.021
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

03:18.105 --> 03:20.730
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

03:20.813 --> 03:21.813
[song trails off]

03:28.855 --> 03:30.855
[eerie, distressing music playing]

03:35.355 --> 03:36.355
[Dante groaning]

03:37.771 --> 03:40.521
You have to keep this safe, always.

03:40.605 --> 03:41.688
You promise?

03:41.771 --> 03:42.771
I promise.

03:43.271 --> 03:45.230
Where's mine? I want mine now.

03:45.313 --> 03:49.438
-Vergil, do you promise to take--
-Yeah, I promise. Give it.

03:50.021 --> 03:50.938
There.

03:51.021 --> 03:53.563
Two perfect halves of a whole.

03:56.105 --> 03:57.855
I think mine's bigger.

03:57.938 --> 03:59.730
No, it's not. Let me see.

04:02.855 --> 04:03.688
Hey.

04:10.480 --> 04:12.563
Okay, boys, that's enough.

04:13.480 --> 04:16.230
I said enough!

04:17.771 --> 04:19.730
[Dante] I'm not sleepy enough.

04:20.480 --> 04:22.021
You're never sleepy.

04:22.605 --> 04:24.896
Why can't you be more like your brother?

04:25.855 --> 04:28.563
Okay, what story do you want tonight?

04:29.355 --> 04:30.730
Tell me about Dad.

04:30.813 --> 04:32.771
Do we get to meet him soon?

04:32.855 --> 04:35.980
All right,
I'll tell you a story about Dad.

04:36.813 --> 04:39.063
But after that you have to go to sleep.

04:40.980 --> 04:42.355
Your dad…

04:45.480 --> 04:46.438
Your dad…

04:47.230 --> 04:49.855
Son of Sparda.

04:50.646 --> 04:52.230
[White Rabbit chuckles]

04:56.313 --> 04:58.355
Why does my head feel like this?

04:58.438 --> 05:01.188
I'd say it's a miracle
it feels like anything.

05:01.271 --> 05:02.313
Enzo?

05:02.396 --> 05:04.105
Hey, good news, kid.

05:04.188 --> 05:05.980
Looks like you're still alive.

05:06.063 --> 05:08.730
The bad news is we're prisoners again.

05:08.813 --> 05:10.563
[captives straining, struggling]

05:14.646 --> 05:16.688
[Baines] So, you did survive the bomb.

05:18.438 --> 05:21.396
By his hand, all things are possible.

05:22.105 --> 05:24.771
I know your voice, and your face.

05:25.563 --> 05:27.646
Aren't you the guy
in those mattress commercials?

05:27.730 --> 05:28.771
Close.

05:29.271 --> 05:30.980
-He's the vice president.
-Oh.

05:32.521 --> 05:34.313
[red demon] You're awake.

05:38.396 --> 05:39.438
Remind me again,

05:39.521 --> 05:42.938
which of you is the Human Torch knockoff,
and which is the talking leaf blower?

05:43.021 --> 05:46.021
You sure you want to be
insulting us right now?

05:46.105 --> 05:49.230
And he's obviously the leaf blower.
Come on!

05:49.771 --> 05:51.563
Agni, the video.

05:51.646 --> 05:54.480
Right. Rabbit left a video for you.

05:54.563 --> 05:57.646
Trust me. It's a good one.

06:00.896 --> 06:02.980
-You've got to put the thing in the--
-I know!

06:03.063 --> 06:05.688
It's not my fault
the humans made the hole too small.

06:05.771 --> 06:09.105
Dante, have you considered
what I told you?

06:09.188 --> 06:11.605
You mean what you said
about my soul being dirty?

06:11.688 --> 06:15.480
I said that God may yet redeem you,
regardless of your origins.

06:15.563 --> 06:19.021
Surely you see
how he must have a plan for you,

06:19.521 --> 06:22.896
to bring you back from the brink of death.

06:23.813 --> 06:28.396
No disrespect, Mr. Vice,
but these guys knew your exact location

06:28.480 --> 06:30.771
and jacked your plane like it was nothing.

06:30.855 --> 06:34.813
I think death's still very much
on the table for all of us.

06:34.896 --> 06:35.730
[Baines] No.

06:36.396 --> 06:38.521
This isn't where my death will come.

06:39.271 --> 06:40.813
How do you know?

06:40.896 --> 06:43.230
Because God will not allow it

06:43.313 --> 06:46.563
until the purpose
he intends for me is fulfilled.

06:46.646 --> 06:48.896
We are all servants of the Lord's plan,

06:49.396 --> 06:51.605
willingly or not.

06:52.105 --> 06:52.938
[Agni] Got it!

06:55.813 --> 06:58.521
Welcome aboard Air Force Two.

06:58.605 --> 07:01.646
We ask that you please
pay attention to the screen

07:01.730 --> 07:04.146
for an important safety announcement.

07:05.063 --> 07:07.438
You're all going to die.

07:10.730 --> 07:14.438
That is,
unless the son of Sparda can save you.

07:14.521 --> 07:16.771
Son of a what? Huh?

07:16.855 --> 07:18.605
[tense, disorienting music playing]

07:18.688 --> 07:19.688
[chuckling smugly]

07:38.313 --> 07:40.771
Looks like the amulet's on the top floor.

07:40.855 --> 07:42.688
Along with the Rabbit, I'm betting.

07:43.188 --> 07:46.271
Strange hideout for a demon bunny.

07:46.355 --> 07:49.813
What did you expect?
Some sort of giant underground burrow?

07:49.896 --> 07:51.896
I mean, I don't know.

07:51.980 --> 07:52.813
Kinda.

07:52.896 --> 07:54.688
Backup's still four minutes out.

07:54.771 --> 07:56.021
We can't wait.

07:56.105 --> 07:58.355
That thing could put the sword
and the amulet together

07:58.438 --> 08:00.480
and end the world anytime it wants.

08:01.355 --> 08:02.771
We go in now.

08:02.855 --> 08:05.271
Take the stairs and stay sharp.

08:05.355 --> 08:07.730
We have to be ready
for any kind of fucked up demon bull--

08:07.813 --> 08:09.063
[resounding thud]

08:10.480 --> 08:11.313
[gasps]

08:12.813 --> 08:13.730
…shit.

08:15.730 --> 08:18.105
This is Ninja for HQ. HQ, do you copy?

08:18.188 --> 08:19.396
[static buzzing]

08:19.480 --> 08:21.896
Anyone? God damn it.

08:21.980 --> 08:24.105
[White Rabbit] Attention all residents.

08:25.646 --> 08:29.730
A terrorist group known as "DARKCOM"
has just entered the building.

08:31.021 --> 08:33.896
Their intentions are extremely hostile.

08:34.438 --> 08:36.230
I'm not asking you to fight them.

08:37.146 --> 08:39.771
I'm simply encouraging it.

08:42.980 --> 08:46.855
Anyone caught engaging with them
in a friendly or neutral manner

08:46.938 --> 08:50.438
will be subject to immediate execution.

08:51.646 --> 08:53.396
Have a great day.

08:53.480 --> 08:55.021
[King] God damn.

08:55.105 --> 08:57.438
Who the hell else
does he have locked in here?

08:57.521 --> 08:59.771
We walked into his own personal fortress.

08:59.855 --> 09:01.646
The mission hasn't changed.

09:01.730 --> 09:05.521
We get to the top floor,
we get the amulet, we get out.

09:05.605 --> 09:07.063
However we can.

09:07.146 --> 09:09.021
We're with you. Let's move.

09:11.771 --> 09:13.771
[foreboding music playing]

09:17.771 --> 09:19.688
Even cut off the communication line.

09:19.771 --> 09:20.688
[slick slithering]

09:21.896 --> 09:26.855
This is way more sophisticated technology
than we've seen any of them use before.

09:26.938 --> 09:28.688
What kind of demon is this?

09:28.771 --> 09:31.521
One slightly worse
than your usual landlord.

09:31.605 --> 09:32.730
-[quivering thrum]
-[squelch]

09:35.313 --> 09:36.188
Sentry?

09:42.980 --> 09:44.105
An energy sword.

09:44.605 --> 09:45.980
[groans] Fascinating.

09:55.146 --> 09:55.980
Fire!

09:56.063 --> 09:57.521
[dark, brooding metal music playing]

10:13.771 --> 10:14.855
[bellows]

10:22.730 --> 10:24.105
Damn it.

10:45.855 --> 10:46.688
I…

11:20.730 --> 11:23.146
Stay with me. Please.

11:27.063 --> 11:28.105
No!

11:28.688 --> 11:29.688
No!

12:05.730 --> 12:06.730
[grunts]

12:07.813 --> 12:08.813
[Mary straining]

12:11.771 --> 12:15.063
[plant demon] Yes, watch them die.

12:15.146 --> 12:21.813
After all, it was you who marched them
straight into our warm embrace.

12:25.605 --> 12:26.730
[gun trilling]

12:27.646 --> 12:29.105
Embrace this.

12:50.063 --> 12:51.355
[seethes]

12:56.313 --> 12:57.230
[panting]

13:01.521 --> 13:02.438
[grunts]

13:06.271 --> 13:08.355
[disorienting, distressing music playing]

13:28.855 --> 13:29.771
Shit.

13:36.188 --> 13:40.021
[White Rabbit] Yes, Dante, I've known
your true origins for some time,

13:40.105 --> 13:44.105
and if you're honest with yourself,
you know it too.

13:44.188 --> 13:47.230
You must have accepted by now
you have demon blood.

13:47.313 --> 13:48.771
Would just any hybrid,

13:48.855 --> 13:52.480
the child of some common brute
and a frail sapien,

13:52.563 --> 13:55.563
be able to do the things you can do?

13:55.646 --> 14:00.146
Why did half of the amulet that Sparda
used to seal the rift between realms

14:00.230 --> 14:01.938
end up as a piece of your jewelry?

14:02.021 --> 14:05.021
The deadbeat father you never met,

14:05.105 --> 14:07.980
who abandoned
your family without a thought,

14:08.063 --> 14:13.021
was the noble and exalted
demon knight Sparda.

14:13.105 --> 14:14.730
Right, Sparda.

14:14.813 --> 14:15.646
Sure thing.

14:15.730 --> 14:17.813
-Can you believe this guy?
-Huh?

14:18.438 --> 14:23.396
I could go on and on listing evidence,
but really, look at you.

14:23.480 --> 14:28.396
Everything about you
marks you as a child of aristocracy.

14:28.480 --> 14:34.396
You know nothing of the pain
and misery in our world,

14:34.480 --> 14:38.521
what your father dooms us to
with his sadistic barrier.

14:39.313 --> 14:42.188
He rebelled against a brutal tyrant,

14:42.271 --> 14:44.980
then locked us in a cell together

14:45.063 --> 14:49.563
while he lived as a hero among humans.

14:50.938 --> 14:54.896
Sparda was nothing
but a narcissistic coward.

14:55.688 --> 14:56.771
[inhales sharply]

14:56.855 --> 14:59.355
You've done his legacy proud.

15:00.896 --> 15:01.730
Damn.

15:01.813 --> 15:04.188
You gonna let him
talk about your dad like that?

15:04.271 --> 15:05.688
[chuckles wryly]

15:05.771 --> 15:06.938
Sorry.

15:07.021 --> 15:08.855
Got off on a tangent there.

15:08.938 --> 15:12.105
The point is, the plane you're on
is rigged with explosives,

15:12.188 --> 15:14.771
which my men will detonate momentarily.

15:14.855 --> 15:19.105
Leaving everyone plunging toward
a squishy and undignified end.

15:19.688 --> 15:21.646
But not to worry,

15:21.730 --> 15:26.105
as Sparda's son, it should be simple
for you to activate your Devil Trigger

15:26.188 --> 15:27.688
and save them all.

15:29.730 --> 15:31.855
I'd bet on it.

15:34.730 --> 15:36.271
[panicked straining]

15:38.521 --> 15:39.563
[Enzo chuckling]

15:41.021 --> 15:46.396
Wow, my good buddy and protégé,
the son of Sparda.

15:47.521 --> 15:52.230
Come on, even if my dad
might have been demon, Sparda isn't real.

15:52.313 --> 15:53.938
He's their version of the boogeyman.

15:54.021 --> 15:55.396
[blue demon] No, he's real.

15:55.480 --> 15:56.855
So real.

15:56.938 --> 16:00.230
Take it from us who've been living
with the fallout of his betrayal

16:00.313 --> 16:01.521
for the last two millennia.

16:01.605 --> 16:03.605
Ha, see? Two millennia.

16:03.688 --> 16:07.605
You really think my dad is a demon
from 200,000 years ago?

16:07.688 --> 16:08.896
How old do I look?

16:08.980 --> 16:13.438
I'm sure you're aware
that demons age differently than humans.

16:13.938 --> 16:18.188
It is entirely possible that Sparda
lived long enough to be your father,

16:18.271 --> 16:19.855
or that he lives still.

16:19.938 --> 16:23.105
Dante, I've always known
you were part demon.

16:24.063 --> 16:26.813
All right, I didn't know. I suspected.

16:26.896 --> 16:29.563
Had an inkling, maybe.

16:29.646 --> 16:31.605
I just couldn't figure how,

16:31.688 --> 16:35.063
but you being Sparda's son
explains everything.

16:35.146 --> 16:36.563
He's the good demon.

16:36.646 --> 16:38.938
He fought for us against them.

16:39.021 --> 16:41.438
That's what's in your blood. You get it?

16:43.105 --> 16:44.355
Let's see if he's right.

16:44.438 --> 16:45.313
You heard Rabbit.

16:45.396 --> 16:49.105
Either you stop us,
or we blow them out of the sky.

16:49.188 --> 16:51.063
It's all right, everyone,

16:51.146 --> 16:54.938
Dante is going to use
that Devil Trigger of his to save us.

16:55.021 --> 16:57.313
What is a Devil Trigger, anyway?

16:57.813 --> 16:58.771
No idea.

16:59.605 --> 17:01.063
Great. We're going to die.

17:01.146 --> 17:02.480
No, we're not.

17:03.188 --> 17:05.480
I don't need any kind of trigger
to beat these two.

17:05.563 --> 17:08.188
What are they going to do?
Form half a Captain Planet?

17:09.021 --> 17:11.480
I wouldn't be so cocky, mate.

17:11.563 --> 17:12.605
After all,

17:13.105 --> 17:16.105
you failed at saving
your own mom and brother.

17:16.188 --> 17:17.021
[Dante gasps]

17:17.105 --> 17:18.646
Oh, yeah.

17:18.730 --> 17:21.271
Rabbit knows all about
what happened to them too.

17:21.355 --> 17:24.980
How you just hid and watched as they died.

17:25.896 --> 17:26.896
[gasps]

17:29.938 --> 17:32.938
I was a helpless kid
when those demons attacked us.

17:35.605 --> 17:37.105
I'm not one anymore.

17:41.563 --> 17:45.813
Well, let's see if we can't
make you feel a little nostalgic.

17:45.896 --> 17:48.438
[rowdy rock music playing]

17:48.521 --> 17:49.521
[music halts]

17:51.146 --> 17:52.146
[coughing]

17:57.438 --> 17:58.730
[gasping]

18:05.396 --> 18:07.271
[tense, distressing music playing]

18:13.563 --> 18:14.563
[coughing]

18:20.605 --> 18:21.813
Lieutenant.

18:23.521 --> 18:25.188
You did this.

18:27.396 --> 18:28.396
[vines creaking]

18:29.271 --> 18:30.313
You killed us.

18:31.521 --> 18:33.313
Just like you killed…

18:34.480 --> 18:35.396
No.

18:52.730 --> 18:53.813
Mary.

18:54.396 --> 18:55.230
Dad?

18:55.730 --> 18:58.188
Look at what you've done.

19:02.813 --> 19:03.813
[Mary yelling]

19:08.188 --> 19:10.188
[distressing music intensifying]

19:15.438 --> 19:18.480
This isn't real. You're not real.

19:21.730 --> 19:22.688
You're real.

19:23.188 --> 19:25.188
[frenetic music building]

19:57.396 --> 19:58.980
[whispers] Go away. Get out of here.

19:59.563 --> 20:00.813
There's nowhere to go.

20:00.896 --> 20:03.855
I know the Rabbit threatened you,
has everyone here hostage,

20:03.938 --> 20:05.980
but there is a demon right behind me.

20:07.771 --> 20:10.563
You're with those soldiers.
We don't want any trouble.

20:10.646 --> 20:12.355
There are no more soldiers.

20:12.438 --> 20:14.438
The demons killed them all.

20:14.521 --> 20:16.771
It's just me. Please.

20:23.855 --> 20:24.980
Quickly.

20:29.188 --> 20:30.188
[knocking at door]

20:30.688 --> 20:31.730
[winged demon] Open.

20:34.188 --> 20:36.646
[winged demon speaking demonic]

20:36.730 --> 20:38.521
No, no. [replying in demonic]

20:39.438 --> 20:40.646
[Mary gasps]

20:43.605 --> 20:45.605
[tense, fraught music playing]

21:09.605 --> 21:12.188
-Now, please, just go and leave us.
-[gun cocks]

21:17.021 --> 21:18.521
[raucous metal music playing]

21:33.813 --> 21:35.563
[Agni] Poor little half-breed.

21:35.646 --> 21:40.646
Gets hit with one measly fireball,
and turns into a whimpering baby.

21:45.313 --> 21:46.146
[klaxon wails]

21:49.480 --> 21:53.355
Seems like that strength Sparda gave you
won't be much use up here.

21:53.438 --> 21:55.771
As useless as the man himself.

21:55.855 --> 21:59.938
The way we heard it, he didn't even
bother showing up to protect you.

22:04.646 --> 22:06.146
[raucous metal music halts]

22:11.480 --> 22:13.896
[muffled] Ooh, watch out for the left!

22:16.855 --> 22:18.521
Look on the bright side.

22:20.855 --> 22:23.105
After watching your whole family die,

22:23.188 --> 22:26.063
watching these people die
should be easy for you.

22:26.146 --> 22:28.146
[raucous metal music pounding]

22:32.438 --> 22:33.646
[mockingly] Aw.

22:33.730 --> 22:36.480
The one time you're fighting
for something other than yourself,

22:37.355 --> 22:39.355
and this is how you do it?

22:43.021 --> 22:45.355
Rabbit was right about you.

22:46.105 --> 22:47.105
[Dante panting]

22:48.563 --> 22:49.688
[blade ringing]

22:49.771 --> 22:51.021
[Dante grunts]

22:53.313 --> 22:55.730
You're just like your dad.

22:55.813 --> 22:57.313
[Agni chuckling]

22:58.063 --> 22:59.063
[muffled thud]

23:01.646 --> 23:03.813
[delicate, disorienting music playing]

23:03.896 --> 23:05.688
[Dante's mother] Your dad…

23:09.230 --> 23:12.021
Your dad was a brave warrior.

23:12.771 --> 23:14.438
The bravest who ever lived.

23:14.938 --> 23:18.480
He fought against all the bad things
so we could be free.

23:19.688 --> 23:21.021
[Dante crying out]

23:23.688 --> 23:25.188
[epic music building]

23:25.271 --> 23:26.188
[Agni] Huh?

23:26.771 --> 23:28.396
[Dante, hoarsely] You're right.

23:29.271 --> 23:30.938
I am like him.

23:41.146 --> 23:43.146
Truly remarkable.

23:44.271 --> 23:46.605
Wow. What is that?

23:47.188 --> 23:49.813
I think this is the Devil Trigger.

23:50.730 --> 23:52.855
Also, I think I'm the son of Sparda.

23:52.938 --> 23:55.146
I've been trying to tell you.

23:56.771 --> 23:59.605
He's ready. Blow the charges.

23:59.688 --> 24:00.771
Yeah.

24:01.355 --> 24:04.146
Just give me a second to kill him first.

24:04.230 --> 24:05.230
[Agni snaps]

24:07.896 --> 24:10.105
We could say he died in the blast.

24:13.480 --> 24:15.480
[forceful rock music playing]

24:27.188 --> 24:29.105
Getting killed with your own sword…

24:35.521 --> 24:36.980
that'd be embarrassing.

24:42.938 --> 24:44.646
Brother!

24:46.855 --> 24:48.771
[disorienting music playing]

24:53.521 --> 24:55.605
We risked everything to hide you.

24:55.688 --> 24:58.313
Now you turn your gun on us? On our kids?

25:00.771 --> 25:04.271
We want nothing from you.
Just leave, please.

25:04.355 --> 25:06.438
Your friend slaughtered my team.

25:07.771 --> 25:09.480
You think we're with…

25:09.980 --> 25:10.980
with them?

25:11.063 --> 25:12.230
She's a sapien.

25:12.313 --> 25:14.896
Of course she thinks
all demons are the same.

25:14.980 --> 25:16.938
If you're not with
the White Rabbit's gang,

25:17.021 --> 25:18.271
why are you here?

25:18.855 --> 25:22.021
We… We needed a way out. He had one.

25:22.605 --> 25:24.230
A way out of where?

25:25.605 --> 25:26.480
Makai.

25:27.438 --> 25:30.646
You call it the Demon Realm, or Hell.

25:30.730 --> 25:31.771
But it's not Hell.

25:31.855 --> 25:32.855
It's worse.

25:33.730 --> 25:36.605
A desolate place, barely suited for life.

25:36.688 --> 25:40.605
And that was before the warlords
ravaged what few resources we had,

25:40.688 --> 25:42.563
and turned the atmosphere toxic.

25:43.396 --> 25:46.271
Only the strongest Makaians
can stand to breathe it.

25:46.771 --> 25:48.146
For those like us…

25:48.813 --> 25:50.313
[Makaian 1] The air itself is poison.

25:51.271 --> 25:53.605
Children rarely survive their first year.

25:54.188 --> 25:56.063
We couldn't accept that fate.

25:56.146 --> 25:57.813
[Mary] Weak-ass sob story.

25:57.896 --> 26:01.271
It doesn't explain how the overgrown
rodent got you into our realm.

26:02.063 --> 26:04.313
With a device that he built.

26:04.396 --> 26:06.146
He showed up with it a year ago,

26:06.230 --> 26:09.271
offering passage to this world
for anyone who wanted.

26:09.355 --> 26:11.396
Dozens of families like us came.

26:12.021 --> 26:14.480
[Makaian 2]
We did it so our children could live,

26:14.563 --> 26:15.938
and live in a better world.

26:16.646 --> 26:20.438
Then we realized,
there is no better world for us.

26:21.063 --> 26:23.313
Sapiens hate and fear our kind.

26:23.896 --> 26:26.855
We'll never be able
to mix openly amongst you.

26:26.938 --> 26:29.438
We have no choice
but to stay here in hiding,

26:29.521 --> 26:31.688
doing whatever that lunatic tells us,

26:31.771 --> 26:34.563
and turning a blind eye to… to his…

26:34.646 --> 26:35.813
To his what?

26:35.896 --> 26:39.438
The children who are orphans,
he does tests on them.

26:39.521 --> 26:40.396
Experiments.

26:40.480 --> 26:41.438
[Mary gasps]

26:41.521 --> 26:43.855
All we're trying to do is survive.

26:43.938 --> 26:45.105
Like you.

26:51.271 --> 26:54.146
I know better
than to trust the words of a demon,

26:56.396 --> 26:58.313
but after everything that's happened,

26:58.396 --> 27:00.313
maybe I don't actually know shit.

27:03.813 --> 27:05.730
My backup should be outside by now.

27:05.813 --> 27:08.730
I'll find a way to get them in,
then I'm going Rabbit hunting.

27:08.813 --> 27:10.938
I'll make sure you're protected.

27:11.021 --> 27:12.521
You and the other…

27:15.396 --> 27:16.396
families.

27:18.021 --> 27:20.021
[raucous rock music building]

27:27.646 --> 27:29.521
You killed my brother.

27:30.396 --> 27:31.730
But unlike yours,

27:32.563 --> 27:34.563
he will have vengeance.

27:34.646 --> 27:35.730
Don't do it.

27:35.813 --> 27:37.230
[panicked exclaiming]

27:37.313 --> 27:38.896
[suspenseful music intensifying]

27:44.188 --> 27:45.313
[beep]

27:47.355 --> 27:48.855
[passengers screaming]

27:53.230 --> 27:55.688
[Dante screaming] Oh, shit!

27:59.105 --> 28:00.105
["Devils Never Cry" plays]

28:00.188 --> 28:01.563
♪ Bless me ♪

28:01.646 --> 28:07.646
♪ With the leaf off of the tree ♪

28:07.730 --> 28:11.563
♪ On it, I see ♪

28:11.646 --> 28:15.521
♪ The freedom reign ♪

28:15.605 --> 28:19.396
♪ We are falling ♪

28:19.480 --> 28:23.230
♪ The light is calling ♪

28:23.313 --> 28:27.146
♪ Tears inside me ♪

28:27.230 --> 28:31.105
♪ Calm me down ♪

28:31.188 --> 28:34.896
♪ Midnight calling ♪

28:34.980 --> 28:38.813
♪ Mist of resolving ♪

28:38.896 --> 28:40.855
♪ Crown me ♪

28:40.938 --> 28:46.688
♪ With the pure, green leaf ♪

28:46.771 --> 28:50.563
♪ Praise to my father ♪

28:50.646 --> 28:54.480
♪ Blessed by the water ♪

28:54.563 --> 28:58.355
♪ Black light, dark sky ♪

28:58.855 --> 29:00.438
IN MEMORY OF KEVIN CONROY (1955-2022)

29:00.521 --> 29:03.313
♪ The devil's cry ♪